# User Journey & App Flow
## Early Emotional Distress Detection & Support App

---

## 1. Overview

This document maps the complete user journey from first discovery to ongoing engagement, including onboarding, daily usage, crisis scenarios, and feature navigation.

---

## 2. User Onboarding Journey

### 2.1 Discovery & Download

**How Users Find the App:**
- App store search ("mental health support," "stress relief," "burnout help")
- Social media campaigns targeting early-career professionals
- Workplace wellness program recommendations
- Word-of-mouth from peers
- Mental health professional recommendations

### 2.2 First Launch Experience

```mermaid
graph TD
    A[App Launch] --> B[Welcome Screen]
    B --> C[Value Proposition]
    C --> D["This app helps you:<br/>✓ Detect stress early<br/>✓ Find immediate support<br/>✓ Connect with peers<br/>✓ Build resilience"]
    D --> E[Important Disclaimer]
    E --> F["⚠️ This app supports well-being<br/>but does NOT diagnose or treat<br/>mental health conditions"]
    F --> G{User Accepts}
    G -->|Yes| H[Privacy & Permissions]
    G -->|No| I[Exit App]
    H --> J[Request Notifications]
    J --> K[Initial Assessment]
```

### 2.3 Initial Assessment (Personalization)

**Purpose:** Tailor app experience to user's primary stressors

**Questions:**

1. **"What brings you here today?"** (Select all that apply)
   - ☐ Work stress and burnout
   - ☐ Family pressure and expectations
   - ☐ Anxiety and overwhelm
   - ☐ Feeling isolated
   - ☐ Just exploring mental health support

2. **"How are you feeling right now?"**
   - 😊 Good
   - 😐 Okay
   - 😞 Not great
   - 😢 Really struggling

3. **"What would help you most?"**
   - Quick stress-relief tools
   - Someone to talk to
   - Understanding my patterns
   - Connecting with others

4. **"Have you experienced thoughts of self-harm or suicide recently?"**
   - No
   - Sometimes
   - Yes, frequently

   > [!CAUTION]
   > If user selects "Yes, frequently" → Immediate crisis intervention screen

**Based on Responses:**
- Customize home screen feature priorities
- Set default notification preferences
- Suggest first actions

### 2.4 Onboarding Completion

```mermaid
graph TD
    A[Assessment Complete] --> B{Crisis Detected?}
    B -->|Yes| C[Emergency Resources Screen]
    B -->|No| D[Personalized Welcome]
    C --> E[Encourage Professional Help]
    E --> F[Optional: Continue to App]
    D --> G[Quick Tutorial]
    G --> H["Swipe through 3 screens:<br/>1. Daily Check-In<br/>2. Emergency Button<br/>3. Explore Features"]
    H --> I[Set Daily Check-In Time]
    I --> J[Home Screen]
    F --> J
```

---

## 3. Daily Usage Scenarios

### 3.1 Routine Day (Low Stress)

**Priya's Morning:**

```mermaid
graph LR
    A[Wake Up] --> B[Check Phone]
    B --> C[See Daily Check-In Notification]
    C --> D[Open App]
    D --> E[Complete Mood Check-In<br/>😊 Good, Stress: 2/5]
    E --> F[Positive Affirmation Shown]
    F --> G[Close App]
    G --> H[Continue Day]
```

**Evening:**
- Brief review of progress tracker
- Read one peer support post
- Close app

**Time Investment:** 3-5 minutes total

---

### 3.2 Stressful Day (Medium Stress)

**Priya's Afternoon:**

```mermaid
graph TD
    A[Stressful Meeting] --> B[Feeling Anxious]
    B --> C[Open App]
    C --> D[Navigate to Mental Health Tools]
    D --> E[Select Box Breathing]
    E --> F[Complete 5-Minute Exercise]
    F --> G[Feel Calmer]
    G --> H{Want More Support?}
    H -->|Yes| I[Open AI Chat]
    H -->|No| J[Return to Work]
    I --> K[Chat About Stress]
    K --> L[AI Validates Feelings]
    L --> M[Suggests Journaling]
    M --> N{Journal Now?}
    N -->|Yes| O[Write Journal Entry]
    N -->|No| P[Save for Later]
    O --> Q[Feel Heard]
    P --> Q
    Q --> J
```

**Evening Check-In:**
- Mood: 😐 Okay, Stress: 4/5
- Log workload: 10-hour day
- App suggests self-care for tomorrow

**Time Investment:** 15-20 minutes total

---

### 3.3 Crisis Day (High Stress/Suicidal Ideation)

**Neha's Late Night:**

```mermaid
graph TD
    A[Overwhelming Thoughts] --> B["I can't do this anymore"]
    B --> C[Open App]
    C --> D[Tap Emergency Button 🚨]
    D --> E[Emergency Resources Screen]
    E --> F{User Choice}
    F -->|Call Helpline| G[Tap AASRA Number]
    F -->|Trusted Contact| H[Call Friend]
    F -->|Safety Plan| I[View Safety Plan]
    G --> J[Connected to Counselor]
    H --> K[Friend Provides Support]
    I --> L[Review Coping Strategies]
    J --> M[Professional Guidance]
    K --> M
    L --> N{Still in Crisis?}
    N -->|Yes| F
    N -->|No| O[Create Safety Plan]
    M --> P[Follow-Up Scheduled]
    O --> P
    P --> Q[Next Day Check-In]
```

**Next Day:**
- App sends: "How are you feeling today?"
- Suggests professional counseling resources
- Offers to help find therapist

**Time Investment:** Variable (crisis-dependent)

