## 5. Detailed User Journeys by Persona

### 5.1 Priya's Journey (Workload Stress)

**Week 1: Discovery**

```mermaid
graph LR
    A[Friend Recommends App] --> B[Downloads App]
    B --> C[Onboarding: Selects Work Stress]
    C --> D[First Mood Check-In: 😐 Stress 4/5]
    D --> E[Explores Workload Tracker]
    E --> F[Logs 65-Hour Week]
    F --> G[Burnout Alert Triggered]
    G --> H[Tries Breathing Exercise]
    H --> I[Feels Slightly Better]
```

**Week 2-3: Building Habit**
- Daily check-ins become routine
- Uses breathing exercises during work breaks
- Reads peer support posts about burnout
- Starts seeing patterns: stress highest on Mondays

**Week 4: Progress**
- Mood improves from 😐 to 🙂
- Stress reduces from 4/5 to 3/5
- App celebrates: "Your stress decreased 25%!"
- Priya feels validated and hopeful

**Month 2: Sustained Use**
- Uses workload data to talk to manager
- Reduces hours to 50/week
- Continues daily check-ins
- Becomes active in peer support community

---

### 5.2 Arjun's Journey (Family Pressure)

**Week 1: Hesitant Start**

```mermaid
graph LR
    A[Searches: Family Pressure Help] --> B[Finds App]
    B --> C[Onboarding: Selects Family Pressure]
    C --> D[First Assessment: High Pressure]
    D --> E[Reads Validation Message]
    E --> F["Finally, someone understands"]
    F --> G[Opens Anonymous Journal]
    G --> H[Writes Suppressed Anger]
    H --> I[Feels Relief]
```

**Week 2-4: Processing Emotions**
- Weekly family assessments
- Regular journaling (3-4 times/week)
- Reads peer stories: "I'm not alone"
- AI chat validates his feelings

**Month 2: Boundary Building**
- Self-care plan suggests boundary-setting
- Practices saying "I need to think about that"
- Family pressure score decreases
- Starts feeling more confident in choices

**Month 3: Transformation**
- Shares anonymous post in peer support
- Receives supportive responses
- Guilt reduces significantly
- Begins to separate his desires from family expectations

---

### 5.3 Neha's Journey (Crisis → Recovery)

**Day 1: Crisis**

```mermaid
graph TD
    A[Panic Attack at Work] --> B[Searches: Suicide Helpline]
    B --> C[Finds App]
    C --> D[Downloads Immediately]
    D --> E[Onboarding: Selects All Stressors]
    E --> F[Assessment: Extremely Struggling]
    F --> G[Crisis Screen Appears]
    G --> H[Calls AASRA Helpline]
    H --> I[Talks to Counselor]
    I --> J[Creates Safety Plan in App]
    J --> K[Adds Trusted Contact: Best Friend]
```

**Week 1: Intensive Support**
- Daily check-ins: Mood still low (😞)
- Uses emergency button 2 more times
- AI chat provides non-judgmental listening
- Starts therapy (app helped find therapist)

**Week 2-4: Gradual Improvement**
- Mood slowly improves: 😞 → 😐
- Uses breathing exercises before meetings
- Workload tracker shows 80+ hour weeks
- Talks to manager about reducing hours

**Month 2-3: Recovery**
- Mood: 😐 → 🙂
- Stress: 5/5 → 3/5
- Working hours: 80 → 55/week
- Continues therapy
- App celebrates: "30 crisis-free days!"

**Month 6: Sustained Well-Being**
- Mood mostly 🙂-😊
- Uses app for maintenance (3-4x/week)
- Active in peer support: Helps others
- Reflects: "This app saved my life"

---

## 6. Crisis Intervention Flow (Detailed)

### 6.1 Crisis Detection Points

**Automatic Detection:**

```mermaid
graph TD
    A[User Interaction] --> B{Crisis Indicators?}
    
    B -->|Mood Check-In| C[😢 + Stress 5/5 + 3+ days]
    B -->|AI Chat| D[Keywords: suicide, die, end it]
    B -->|Journal Entry| E[Self-harm language detected]
    B -->|Peer Support Post| F[Crisis content flagged]
    B -->|Manual| G[User Taps Emergency Button]
    
    C --> H[Trigger Crisis Protocol]
    D --> H
    E --> H
    F --> H
    G --> H
    
    H --> I[Emergency Resources Screen]
```

### 6.2 Crisis Intervention Screen

**Immediate Display:**

```
┌─────────────────────────────────────┐
│  🚨 You Don't Have to Face This    │
│     Alone                           │
│                                     │
│  We're concerned about you. Please  │
│  reach out to someone who can help: │
│                                     │
│  ═══════════════════════════════   │
│                                     │
│  📞 Crisis Helplines (24/7)         │
│                                     │
│  [Call AASRA]                       │
│  91-22-27546669                     │
│                                     │
│  [Call Vandrevala Foundation]       │
│  1860-2662-345                      │
│                                     │
│  [Call iCall]                       │
│  91-22-25521111                     │
│                                     │
│  ═══════════════════════════════   │
│                                     │
│  👤 Your Trusted Contact            │
│  [Call Sarah (Best Friend)]         │
│                                     │
│  ═══════════════════════════════   │
│                                     │
│  📋 [View My Safety Plan]           │
│                                     │
│  ═══════════════════════════════   │
│                                     │
│  [I'm Safe Now] [Create Safety Plan]│
└─────────────────────────────────────┘
```

### 6.3 Post-Crisis Follow-Up

```mermaid
graph TD
    A[Crisis Event Logged] --> B[Wait 24 Hours]
    B --> C[Send Check-In Notification]
    C --> D["How are you feeling today?"]
    D --> E{User Response}
    E -->|Still in Crisis| F[Show Resources Again]
    E -->|Improving| G[Encourage Professional Help]
    E -->|No Response| H[Send Reminder After 12 Hours]
    F --> I[Suggest Therapy Finder]
    G --> I
    H --> J{Response?}
    J -->|Yes| E
    J -->|No After 48hrs| K[Log for Concern]
```

---

## 7. Notification Strategy

### 7.1 Notification Types

| Type | Frequency | Example | Dismissible |
|------|-----------|---------|-------------|
| **Daily Check-In** | Once daily (user-set time) | "How are you feeling today?" | Yes |
| **Burnout Alert** | When triggered | "You've worked 60+ hours for 3 weeks" | No |
| **Self-Care Reminder** | 2-3x/week | "Time for your breathing exercise" | Yes |
| **Milestone Celebration** | When achieved | "🎉 7 days of check-ins!" | No |
| **Crisis Follow-Up** | 24hrs after crisis | "Checking in on you. How are you?" | No |
| **Peer Support Reply** | When someone replies | "Someone responded to your post" | Yes |

### 7.2 Notification Timing

**Smart Scheduling:**
- Avoid late night (11 PM - 7 AM) unless crisis
- Respect "Do Not Disturb" settings
- Adapt to user's engagement patterns

---

## 8. Accessibility Considerations

### 8.1 Visual Accessibility
- High contrast mode
- Adjustable font sizes (150%, 200%)
- Screen reader compatibility
- Color-blind friendly palette

### 8.2 Motor Accessibility
- Large tap targets (minimum 44x44 pixels)
- Voice input for journaling
- Swipe gestures optional (button alternatives)

### 8.3 Cognitive Accessibility
- Simple, clear language
- Consistent navigation
- Minimal steps to critical features
- Visual progress indicators

---

## 9. Offline Functionality

**Available Offline:**
- ✅ Daily mood check-in (syncs when online)
- ✅ Breathing exercises
- ✅ Grounding techniques
- ✅ Journal entries
- ✅ View saved safety plan
- ✅ Emergency helpline numbers (cached)

**Requires Internet:**
- ❌ AI chat
- ❌ Peer support community
- ❌ Progress sync across devices

---

## 10. User Journey Success Metrics

### 10.1 Onboarding Success
- **Target:** 80% complete onboarding
- **Metric:** % of downloads that complete initial assessment

### 10.2 Engagement
- **Target:** 60% DAU (Daily Active Users)
- **Metric:** % of users who complete daily check-in

### 10.3 Feature Adoption
- **Target:** 70% use 3+ features
- **Metric:** % of users engaging with multiple features

### 10.4 Crisis Support
- **Target:** 90% access helpline when in crisis
- **Metric:** % of crisis events resulting in helpline call

### 10.5 Retention
- **Target:** 70% retention at 3 months
- **Metric:** % of users still active after 90 days

---

## Conclusion

The user journey is designed to:

✅ **Minimize friction** to critical features (emergency button, check-in)  
✅ **Build habits** through daily engagement  
✅ **Provide immediate support** in crisis moments  
✅ **Adapt to user needs** through personalization  
✅ **Encourage long-term use** through progress tracking  

Every flow prioritizes **user safety, privacy, and emotional well-being** above all else.

---

